README

Bash dot files used for interactive user on Ubuntu

I have this setup:

    $ git clone git@github.com:stav/dotfiles.git
    $ mv -r dotfiles ~/.bash
    $ for file in ~/.bash; do ln -s ".bash/$file" "~/$file"; done;

.bashrc

	Just source .bash_profile

.bash_profile

	* Add ~/bin to PATH

	* Source all of these files if they exist:

		** ~/.bash_path
		** ~/.bash_prompt
		** ~/.bash_exports
		** ~/.bash_aliases
		** ~/.bash_functions
		** ~/.bash_extra

	* Setup some history stuff and bash-completion
